<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[263,647,897,952]" box="[384,526,929,952]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
(
<figureCitation box="[392,467,929,952]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[836,872,2033,2054]" captionTargetBox="[839,1469,1040,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-452@6.[829,1480,1033,2013]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 6. Pithemera fusiformis, new species: A, ventral view; B, spermathecae and diverticulum. Scale bars = 3 mm (A), 1 mm (B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4509229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4509229/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
A–B)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[835,1474,193,344]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Septa 5/6–7/8 thin, 8/9 absent, 9/10–13/14 thin. Gizzard in viii–ix, intestine enlarged from xv; intestinal caeca simple, originating in xxii, and extending anteriorly about to xxi, each consisting of a small sac, laterally placed; typhlosole none. Hearts xi–xiii esophageal; ix lateral.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[835,1474,385,632]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Ovaries and funnels in xiii, spermatheca in v–ix; no nephridia on spermathecal ducts; spermatheca with small ampulla, duct longer than ampulla, diverticulum sausage-shaped, shorter than ampulla. Male sexual system holandric, testes and funnels in paired lateral sacs in x, xi, not connected. Seminal vesicles two pairs in xi, xii with dorsal lobes. Prostates in xvii–xix, one or two lobes; prostatic duct with spindle-shaped muscular expansion in ectal half.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[835,1474,673,888]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,961,673,697]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Remarks. –</emphasis>
The species also keys to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Perrier" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[1287,1373,673,696]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Pithemera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bicincta">
<emphasis box="[1287,1373,673,696]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">bicincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in Sims &amp; Easton (1972), but 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Perrier" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[1151,1280,705,728]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Pithemera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bicincta">
<emphasis box="[1151,1280,705,728]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Pi. bicincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Beddard" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1340,1473,705,728]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Pithemera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis box="[1340,1473,705,728]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Pi. violacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the ampulla longer than the diverticulum and different locations of genital papillae. 
<taxonomicName authority="Hong &amp; James, 2011" authorityName="Hong &amp; James" authorityYear="2011" box="[1173,1410,769,792]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Pithemera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusiformis" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[1173,1410,769,792]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Pithemera fusiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="6" pageNumber="25" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
is greatly smaller than 
<taxonomicName authority="Hong &amp; James, 2011" authorityName="Hong &amp; James" authorityYear="2011" box="[1199,1409,801,824]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Pithemera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="glandis" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[1199,1409,801,824]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">Pithemera glandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="6" pageNumber="25" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, (20–22 vs. 
<quantity box="[1055,1190,833,856]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.8" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="85.0" valueMax="108.0" valueMin="62.0">62–108 mm</quantity>
), has genital papillae and also lacks a typhlosole.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
